{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b20428ba-b3fe-431a-a1c8-ce27e8a5aebc","content":"The directory is empty — no files to modify. I'll show you exactly what to change and how to catch errors at build time.\n\n### Converting to compiled bindings\n\nAdd `x:DataType` to your `ContentPage` element, pointing at your ViewModel:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\"\n                     Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"36\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe **only structural change** is adding two attributes to `<ContentPage>`:\n1. **`xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"`** — imports the namespace.\n2. **`x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"`** — enables compiled bindings for the entire page.\n\nAll existing `{Binding ...}` expressions stay the same — the compiler now resolves them against `SettingsViewModel` at build time.\n\n### Catching binding errors at build time\n\nWith `x:DataType` in place, mistyped or missing properties (e.g. `{Binding Themee}`) already produce **build errors** — no extra configuration needed.\n\nTo go further and **fail on warnings**, add this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Treat all XC* (XAML compiler) warnings as errors -->\n  <WarningsAsErrors>$(WarningsAsErrors);XC0045</WarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n`XC0045` is the diagnostic for \"property not found on the data type.\" This turns it into a hard build error so CI pipelines can't miss it.\n\n### Quick rules to remember\n\n| Situation | What to do |\n|---|---|\n| Whole page uses one VM | `x:DataType` on `<ContentPage>` |\n| A child section uses a different type | `x:DataType` on that container element |\n| Need to opt out (e.g. dynamic binding) | `x:DataType=\"x:Null\"` on that element |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6c293696-dba6-4c64-a973-893e1e74029c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty. The user is asking about a file that doesn't exist yet. They're describing a scenario and want guidance on how to convert their XAML page to use compiled bindings. Let me provide the guidance directly.","outputTokens":795,"requestId":"DBC6:7AD2E:803C4:A0BAA:69F549F4"},"id":"4a75e3eb-f59d-458c-a5a7-5b2db030ed63","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:49:09.329Z","parentId":"e14354fe-6ba0-4a5e-b03b-d6a83b311892"}
